ee the start of a major reversal in the trend which will ultimately open the door for a more significant decline over the medium-term. In the interim, look for the market to hold below 1.0800 on a weekly close basis, and for the formation of a lower top below 1.1080 ahead of the next downside extension back below 0.9925. A break back below 1.0360 will help to confirm outlook, while only a weekly close beyond 1.0800 negates.    </span>\n</p><p class="gsstx"></p><p class="gsstx"></p><p class="gsstx" style="text-align:justify">\n<span class="gsstx" style="font-size:12px;font-weight:bold;">Written by Joel Kruger, Technical Currency Strategist for DailyFX.com </span>\n</p><p class="gsstx" style="text-align:justify">\n<span class="gsstx" style="font-size:12px;font-weight:bold;">If you wish to receive Joel's reports in a more timely fashion, e-mail </span><a href="mailto:jskruger@dailyfx.com" class="gsstx"><span class="gsstx" style="font-size:12px;text-decoration:underline;">jskruger@dailyfx.com</span></a><span class="gsstx" style="font-size:12px;font-weight:bold;"> and you will be added to the "</span><span class="gsstx" style="font-size:12px;font-weight:bold;">distribution" </span><span class="gsstx" style="font-size:12px;font-weight:bold;">list.</span>\n</p><p class="gsstx" style="text-align:justify">\n<span class="gsstx" style="font-size:12px;font-weight:bold;"> If you wish to discuss this topic or any other feel free to visit our </span><a href="http://forexforums.dailyfx.com/" class="gsstx"><span class="gsstx" style="font-size:12px;font-weight:bold;">Forum page</span></a>\n</p><p class="gsstx"></p>\n\n</div></div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<p style="font: italic 11px/20px Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: center; ">DailyFX provides <a href="http://www.dailyfx.com/" title="Forex Market News and Analysis by DailyFX">forex news</a> on the economic reports and political events that influence the currency market.<br />\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tLearn <a href="htt