enttext">\r\n\t\t\t<div style="float:left;margin:0px 10px 10px 0px;"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/ef9d5dcc6485784fcfa06121cb8e3b0b?s=60&amp;d=retro&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-60 photo' height='60' width='60' /></div><p>Hope all EURUSD bulls enjoying the ride. Your problem is that many of you made some buck during the steady EURUSD rallies in the past and now on every dip you hope for the same freebie. Well, I think these are different times.</p>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\r\n\t\t\t</div>\r\n\r\n\t\t</li>\r\n\r\n\t\r\n\t\r\n\t\t<li class="" id="comment-254427">\r\n\t\t\tGerry Davies on\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\tSeptember 9th, 2011 10:24 GMT \r\n\t\t\t<div class="commenttext">\r\n\t\t\t<div style="float:left;margin:0px 10px 10px 0px;"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/c336bf81c7206f7cc42faa7f7ab7ca63?s=60&amp;d=retro&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-60 photo' height='60' width='60' /></div><p>Personally, I think 1.3750 might be a step too far this week TC, but who knows given the current momentum. Once again apologies. I&#8217;ll certainly be having my first pop of the week fairly soon&#8230;&#8230;.</p>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\r\n\t\t\t</div>\r\n\r\n\t\t</li>\r\n\r\n\t\r\n\t\r\n\t</ol>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<form action="http://www.forexlive.com/wp-comments-post.php" method="post" id="commentform">\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><label style="color:#333;" for="name">Your name (required)</label><br />\r\n<input type="text" name="author" id="name" value="" size="60" tabindex="1" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><label style="color:#333;" for="email">Email (required)</label><br />\r\n<input type="text" name="email" id="email" value="" size="60" tabindex="2" />\r\n<div style="color:#e40e62; font-size:10px;">The content of this field will not be shown publicly.</div></p>\r\n\r\n<p><label style="color:#333;" for="url">Homepage</label><br />\r\n<input type="text" name="url" id="url" value="" size="60" tabindex="3" /></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<!--<p><small><strong>XHTML:</stro