d hammered the single currency.\n\nBarrier option interestÂ well noted at 1.3850 and defence of said interest slowed the sell-off, but only temporarily and eventually we took out 1.3800 barrier interest as well before some limited recovery. Â \n\nNasty morning for aussie, AUD/USD down at 1.0525 from early 1.0615.Â  Much talk of decent fix interest to buy the GBP/AUD cross this morning. As I type this we're up a big figure at 1.1560 from when we first reported the interest.Â  HOW BLOODY COOL ARE WE!!!!!Â  Unfortunately not sure what this interest was related to.\n\nCable down onlyÂ mariginally at 1.5945 from early 1.5975 againstÂ the backdrop of burgeoning dollar strength, no doubt helped by the aforementioned GBP/AUD buy interest.\n\nUSD/CHF up atÂ .8790 from early .8720, EUR/CHFÂ steady atÂ 1.2140.\n\nPersonally I've had more than a belly full for this week.Â  Hope you've all survived and maybe even prospered. Roll on the weekend!!!!!!!</div>\r\n    </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="article-footer">\r\n    \r\n\t\r\n    <div class="section"><a href="http://www.forexlive.com" target="_blank"><img src="http://mediaserver.fxstreet.com/images/forexlive-provider-logo-en.jpeg" alt="Forex Live" /></a></div>\r\n    <br />\r\n    \r\n    <div class="section module-advertisement selfpromo4">\r\n    <div class="module-title"><strong>Advertisement</strong></div>\r\n\t<div class="p10 typo">\r\n\t<a href="http://adserver.fxstreet.com/Servidor/adClick.aspx?siteId=21&amp;serviceId=3954&amp;path=/default.aspx&amp;adId=6910&amp;linkId=6519"><strong >Transfer money globally at the same rates as corporations</strong></a>\r\n\t<p>Make significant savings on your international money transfers using FXstreet.com's Global Transfers.</p>\r\n\t</div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    \r\n\t<br />\r\n\t<div class="section">\r\n\t\t<div class="disclaimer"> \r\n\t\t\t\tThe opinions and analysis offered on Forexlive are for educational purposes only and clients and prospects are advised to careful