   <tr>\n                <td class="mainbox">\n                                        <table class="contentpaneopen">\n<tr>\n\t\t<td class="contentheading" width="100%">\n\t\t\t\t<a href="/action-insight/market-overview/european-session:-orders-and-options-watch-20110907148317/" class="contentpagetitle">\n\t\t\tEuropean Session: Orders and Options Watch</a>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t<td align="right" width="100%" class="buttonheading">\n\t\t<a href="/action-insight/market-overview/european-session:-orders-and-options-watch-20110907148317/print/?tmpl=component" title="Print" onclick="window.open(this.href,'win2','status=no,toolbar=no,scrollbars=yes,titlebar=no,menubar=no,resizable=yes,width=640,height=480,directories=no,location=no'); return false;" rel="nofollow"><img src="/images/M_images/printButton.png" alt="Print"  /></a>\t\t</td>\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\t<td align="right" width="100%" class="buttonheading">\n\t\t<a href="/mailto/?link=58fa6eb8f0824620fc32d8b64764cdf68613da93?tmpl=component" title="E-mail" onclick="window.open(this.href,'win2','width=400,height=350,menubar=yes,resizable=yes'); return false;"><img src="/images/M_images/emailButton.png" alt="E-mail"  /></a>\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n</table>\n\n<table class="contentpaneopen">\n\n<tr>\n\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class="small">\n\t\t\t\t\t\tMarket Overview\t\t\t\t\t| </span>\n\t\t\n\t\t<span class="small">\n\t\t\tWritten by ActionForex.com\t\t| </span>\n\n\t<span class="createdate">\n\t\tSep 07 11 06:49 GMT\t\t</span>\n</tr>\n\n\n<tr>\n<td valign="top">\n<div class='contad'><iframe id='a333fd69' name='a333fd69'  src='http://ads.actionforex.net/adframe.php?n=a333fd69&what=zone:7&target=_blank' framespacing='0' frameborder='no' scrolling='no' width='300' height='250' allowtransparency='true'><a href='http://ads.actionforex.net/adclick.php?n=a333fd69' target='_blank'><img src='http://ads.actionforex.net/adview.php?what=zone:7&n=a333fd69' border='0' alt=''></a></iframe></div>\r\n<h1>European Session: Orders and Options Watch</h1>\r\n<p> JPY: Despite rising marginally to 77.72 (just 2 ticks above previous resistance), the greenback ran into indicated heavy offers from exporters and has retreated as BOJ disappointed markets with no new easing measures announced. Traders quickly squared their long USD/JPY positions and the pair dropped to as low as 77.07 after the BOJ rate decision.  As stated in our previous update bids from Japanese corps and margin accounts have been raised to 77.00-10 and buying interest is still noted in this level and also 76.70 with stops placed below 76.40, 76.20 and further out at 75.90 (large). On the upside, stops remain at 77.80 with offers ahead of this level at 77.60-70 and more selling interest should emerge around 78.00 (option trigger) and 78.20.</p>\r\n<p>CHF: The greenback also rose marginally above yesterday&rsquo;s high of 0.8627 to 0.8630 this morning before retreating on back of weakness in EUR/CHF, which retreated from 1.2080 to 1.2036 (it looks like EUR/CHF could not go too far away of the 1.2000 minimum rate). Although USD/CHF also slipped to 0.8560/62, bids are reported at 0.8540/45 and further out at 0.8500, more buying interest should emerge around 0.8450 and 0.8400. On the upside, some offers are tipped at 0.8600 and also 0.8630 which may cap the upside before U.S. opening. </p>\r\n<p>EUR: The single currency recovered after holding above yesterday&rsquo;s low of 1.3972 on dollar&rsquo;s broad-based retreat and offers at 1.4050-60 were absorbed and mixture of offers and stops is located at 1.4090-00, however, more selling interest should emerge from 1.4130 up to 1.4170 and 1.4200. On the downside, bids from short-term specs are noted at 1.4040-50 and 1.4000-10 with stops building up below 1.3970-80 and more sizeable stops are tipped below 1.3950 option barrier. </p>\r\n<p>GBP: Cable edged higher as well in Asia on short-covering ahead of the release of UK industrial and manufacturing production data (08:30GMT) and offers at 1.6000 are likely to be filled. Improved risk appetite as Asian equities rebounded (Nikkei up 2% and HIS rose 300 points) also helped supporting sterling but more selling interest should emerge further out at 1.6050-60 and 1.6100-10. However, with recent soft economic data releases out of UK, cable&rsquo;s upside is likely to be limited as some traders are expecting the production data to come weaker than expected. ON the downside, light bids are noted at 1.5960-70 and mixture of bids and stops is seen at 1.5930-40 with more stops placed below 1.5920 and 1.5900. </p>\r\n<p>AUD: Aussie rebounded quite strongly this morning on upbeat data and comments from officials but offers in good size are still noted at 1.0620 and it needs to trigger stops at 1.0630 in order to push AUD/USD further north. On the downside, bids are reported from 1.0570 down to 1.0530.</p></td>\n</tr>\n\n</table>\n<span class="article_separator">&nbsp;</span>\n\n                                        \t<div class="bot1"></div>\n                    \t<div class="bot2a">\t\t<div class="moduletable-artlist">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h3>Latest in Market Overview</h3>\n\t\t\t\t\t\n<!-- START 'Display News by BK 1.6.7' -->\n\n<span class='dn-whole-artlist '>\n</span><ul><li class='arrow-dn-artlist '><span class='dn-date-artlist '>Sep 09 06:44 GMT</span> - <span class='dn-head-artlist '><a  href='/action-insight/market-overview/european-session:-orders-and-options-watch-20110909148526/' class='dn-title-artlist ' >European Session: Orders and Optio...</a></span>\n<div style="clear: both;"></div></li><li class='arrow-dn-artlist '><span class='dn-date-artlist '>Sep 09 06:24 GMT</span> - <span class='dn-head-artlist '><a  href='/action-insight/market-overview/daily-report:-muted-reaction-to-obama%27s-job-proposal,-euro-continues-post-ecb-weakness-20110909148517/' class='dn-title-artlist ' >Daily Report: Muted Reaction to Ob...</a></span>\n<div style="clear: both;"></div></li><li class='arrow-dn-artlist '><span class='dn