sdayâs speeches from President Barack Obama and Federal Reserve Chairman Ben Bernanke out of the way, âwe now shift focus to the G-7 meeting, which kicks off today and concludes tomorrow,â said Adam Cole, global head of foreign-exchange strategy at RBC Capital Markets.</p>\n<p>âExpectations of anything material coming out of the meeting have gradually deflated in recent days,â he noted, with officials quoted as saying no announcement will be issued at the finale of the meeting.</p>\n<p>Cole said that still, there may be some residual hope that officials will put some meat onto their Aug. 9 pledge to âtake all necessary measures to support financial stability and growth in a spirit of close cooperation, but specifics seem increasingly unlikely.</p>\n<p>Analysts said that overall market feedback to Obamaâs jobs speech late Thursday night was undemonstrative and reserved. Obama advised a $440 billion package of tax cuts and other spurs he said would âjoltâ the biggest global economy back into growth.</p>\n<p>Meanwhile, the<strong> euro EURUSD </strong>-1.12% sustained to crush lower after breaching the $1.40 level on Thursday. The euro procured $1.3812 in recent action, down from $1.3884 in late North American trading Thursday.</p>\n<p>The shared currency came under stress after Jean-Claude Trichet, president of the European Central Bank, indicated that the bankâs cycle of interest-rate hikes had likely come to an end along with a restraining inflation outlook and escalating downside risks to growth.</p>\n<p>âWe would not regard this as an indication that the ECB is about to ease, only that they are likely to remain on hold,â said Adrian Schmidt, currency strategist at Lloyds TSB in London. âBut the continued concern about Greece maintains the negative euro tone.â</p>\n<p>Also Friday, the <strong>British pound GBPUSD</strong> -0.38%  traded at $1.5957, little changed from $1.5965.</p>\n<p>The dollar raised to 77.84 yen versus the <strong>Japanese currency USDJPY</strong> +0.32% , up from Â¥77.52. </p>\n<script type="text/javascript">AKPC_IDS += "6088,";</script><p class="akpc_pop">Popularity: 1% <span class="akpc_help">[<a href="http://alexking.org/projects/wordpress/popularity-contest" title="What does this mean?">?</a>]</span></p>\r\n\t\r\n\r\n\t<div style="float: left; width: 320px; height: 270px; margin-top: 40px;"><script type="text/javascript"><!--\r\ngoogle_ad_client = "pub-6730133815996727";\r\n/* Single Post (Bottom) */\r\ngoogle_ad_slot = "3382578324";\r\ngoogle_ad_width = 300;\r\ngoogle_ad_height = 250;\r\n//-->\r\n</script>\r\n<script type="text/javascript"\r\nsrc="http://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/show_ads.js">\r\n</script></div>\r\n\r\n\t<div style=" ">\t<style>\r\n\r\n\t\t\t.clinks { color:#92CEDF !important; text-decoration:none  !important;}\r\n\r\n\t\t\t.clinks:hover { color:#ddd  !important; text-decoration:underline !important; }\r\n\r\n\t\t\t</style>\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t<div style="  padding:16px;" class="news">\r\n\r\n\t\t\t<div style="font-weight: bold; color:white; font-size:15px">You may be intresting in:</div>\r\n\r\n\t\t\r\n\r\n           \r\n\r\n              <ul style="list-style:none;">\r\n\r\n                    \r\n    <li style="padding: 3px; "><span style=" padding:9px;background:url('http://www.usamarketnews.com/wp-content/themes/usamarketnews/images/arrow2.png') no-repeat scroll 0 10px transparent;">&nbsp;</span><span style="margin-left:9px;"><a class="clinks" href="http://www.usamarketnews.com/forex-news/6028/euro-reported-the-fall-after-trichet%e2%80%99s-comments.html" rel="bookmark" title="Euro Reported the Fall after Trichetâs Comments">Euro Reported the Fall after Trichetâs Comments</a>\r\n\r\n</span>    </li>\r\n\r\n\r\n    \r\n    <li style="padding: 3px; "><span style=" padding:9px;background:url('http://www.usamarketnews.com/wp-content/themes/usamarketnews/images/arrow2.png') no-repeat scroll 0 10px transparent;">&nbsp;</span><span style="margin-lef